
'''= The iWorkers Union unites and represents internet, information technology, and remote presence workers around the world with one clear voice. We encourage industry and service sector standardization, and classification of job descriptions, and working conditions across a broad range of internet employment situations.'''

URL = http://www.newcentra.org/iworkersunion/index.htm


=Description=

    * The iWorkers Union is fully web site based, here at iworkersunion.org.
    * The iWorkers Union International was chartered in 2008.
    * There is no large physical office, or headquarters, at this time.
    * This is a non-profit organization, funded only through modest registration fees, dues, and donations by members, and concerned groups around the world.
    * This union is not associated with any other entity, and exists for purposes of, and by the grace of, its membership Manifesto and Charter only.
    * The Preamble, Manifesto, and Charter are posted on this web site.
    * The organization structure is detailed in the iWorkers Union Operating Manual, currently in production.
    * The Executive members are from around the world, and are elected.
    * The current president-elect of the iWorkers Union is Allan William Clark 1.0, of Victoria, B.C., Canada.
    * The schedule for the first iWorkers Union on-line elections is as follows:
    * Regional delegates - September 2011.
    * Elections for international directors - December 2011.

